<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-02T19:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-02T19:34:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1740</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moser</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-03T09:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">May 3,
                                            1918, 9 a.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 5, 1.48
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Officially [announced] that <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> force has advanced to right bank of Onon
                                River. As force nearly doubled by Cossacks, volunteers <pb facs="0241" n="151" xml:id="pg_151"/> will endeavor to cross
                                Onon and hold station of Olovyannaya ninety miles east of Karymskaya
                                [omission] and await there the receipt of further arms from Japan
                                including armored [cars] now <hi rend="italic">en route</hi>, also
                                help, before undertaking to advance beyond junction. Has now
                                advanced appliances [headquarters] one mile west of Manchuria
                                [Station] and has requested Chinese Eastern Railway to assume
                                operation of [omission] lines as he advances. Is still receiving
                                money and arms from British and Japanese Governments. His advance
                                has aroused enthusiasm and force is said to have [increased] for
                                past ten days.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_MCK1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Moser</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>